<div id="review_3948530798" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3948530798" />
    <a title="Mary Cowley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/112350006-mary-cowley"><img alt="Mary Cowley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585860621p2/112350006.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3948530798?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary Cowley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary Cowley" href="/user/show/112350006-mary-cowley">Mary Cowley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3948530798" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5380269443687287430">Nice idea but I can’t say he really gives it wings. Cookies, for example. He gives the ratio and then half a dozen recipes where the ratio has been changed. I understand that if you know the ratio you can proceed without a recipe, but he then gives us several recipes,.Or change the cookie by adding different flavorings and ingredients. It frees you to make something unique - but at what point does that ratio bend beyond recognition? In which case, it’s just not a valid ratio to start with. Basic</span>
  <span id="freeText5380269443687287430" style="display:none">Nice idea but I can’t say he really gives it wings. Cookies, for example. He gives the ratio and then half a dozen recipes where the ratio has been changed. I understand that if you know the ratio you can proceed without a recipe, but he then gives us several recipes,.Or change the cookie by adding different flavorings and ingredients. It frees you to make something unique - but at what point does that ratio bend beyond recognition? In which case, it’s just not a valid ratio to start with. Basically, the idea has merit, but like I said, he doesn’t really give it wings. Great for a beginning cook, but if you’re been cooking and baking for 50 years, it doesn’t add much to what you know or how you’ll cook.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5380269443687287430" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
